## Wiki Reading Protocol

**Always check the wiki before investigating.** Prior knowledge prevents duplicate
work and provides crucial context (known offsets, struct layouts, version-specific
notes).

```bash
# Check wiki index for related entries
cat {{ .Env.WIKI_DIR }}/index.md

# Search for target-related pages
grep -rl "<search_term>" {{ .Env.WIKI_DIR }}/

# Read relevant pages before forming plans
cat {{ .Env.WIKI_DIR }}/<relevant_page>.md
```

When reading wiki entries:
- Note what is **already known** (do not re-derive)
- Note what is **contradictory** (needs verification)
- Note what is **missing** (your investigation targets)
- Note the **binary version** for each finding (offsets shift between patches)

